1.title: Petra
1.plot: The Go Jetters have to save the ancient city of Petra when Glitch causes an earthquake.

2.title: The Matterhorn
2.plot: Glitch puts the Go Jetters and other mountaineers in danger when he decides to descend Mount Matterhorn.

3.title: Bonneville Salt Flats
3.plot: Xuli and Glitch go head to head as they try to beat the Go Jet Academy land speed record.

4.title: Rainforests of Sumatra, Indonesia
4.plot: The Go Jetters much save the world's stinkiest plant from becoming Glitch's new perfume.

5.title: Go Jet Academy: Artificial Reef
5.plot: When she finds a shipwreck on a coral reef, Xuli learns that not all glitches need fixing.

6.title: Machu Picchu
6.plot: The Go Jetters must stop a giant Grimbot bouncing down the valley of Machu Picchu.

7.title: Avenue of the Baobabs
7.plot: A baby lemur needs rescuing when Glitch's HQ crashes into the baobabs.

8.title: Venice
8.plot: Glitch turns the Canals of Venice into roads.

9.title: Seattle Space Needle
9.plot: The team goes where no Go Jetter has gone before, when Glitch tries to launch into space by attaching huge rocket boosters.

10.title: Go Jet Academy: Hailstorm
10.plot: The Go Jetters join Ubercorn in the Go Jet Academy to try out a brand new super vacuum that reportedly can suck up bad weather. But can it save the Go Jet Academy from a glitched thunderstorm?

11.title: Harbin Ice City
11.plot: Grim HQ overheats and lands in Harbin Ice City, melting in the process the amazing ice sculptures.

12.title: Dover
12.plot: The team race to save the White Cliffs of Dover when Glitch digs for classroom chalk.

13.title: Central Park, New York
13.plot: Glitch visits Broadway while the Go Jetters tackle a huge cloud of smog in Central Park.

14.title: Bullet Train, Japan
14.plot: Glitch wonders where his grimbots have gone. Some excited bleeps further down a rail platform reveal that they have jumped into the driver's cabin of a bullet train, they steal it and then they press all the buttons.

15.title: Go Jet Academy: Wind Power
15.plot: When his kite comes to close to the academy's windfarm, the Go Jetters must save Glitch.

16.title: Gua Rusa, Borneo
16.plot: Glitch scoops up all the guano of Gua Rusa to grow his Halloween pumpkin in just one day.

17.title: Christmas Island, Indian Ocean
17.plot: The Go Jetters snap into action as Glitch seeks some festive cheer on Christmas Island.

18.title: Terracotta Army, China
18.plot: Ubercorn shuts down Glitch's raucous rock performance leaving the Grandmaster determined to find a brand new crowd who'll love his loud music. He decides to travel to Chian in China. Can the Go Jetters stop Glitch's noisy guitar and save the Terracotta Army in China?

19.title: Panama Canal, Panama
19.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is late for the European Moustache of the Year award ceremony. However, attempting to jump the Panama Canal leaves him with a sinking feeling. And even worse, his Grimbler breaks down.

20.title: Tower Bridge, London
20.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is visiting London and spots the perfect souvenir at a riverside stall. But when he finds he has no money, he decides to raise some by working as a tour guide on the River Thames.

21.title: Tepui Mountains, Venezuela
21.plot: Foz, Kyan and Lars are climbing a Tepui in Venezuela, with Xuli exploring this amazing place in her Vroomster. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is lost and looking for his Grimbots in the thick clouds around the Tepui. He flies up and collides with the Vroomster.

22.title: Go Jet Academy: Biogas Power
22.plot: Glitch is excited when Lars refits the Grimbler with new, clean bio-gas boosters that could make it even faster than the Vroomster.

23.title: Go Jet Academy: Hurricane Rescue
23.plot: Grim HQ struggles through the sky above the Atlantic Ocean, fighting against the powerful winds of a hurricane. One Grimbot falls overboard before the ship crash-lands at Go Jet Academy. Needing another ship to rescue the missing Grimbot, Glitch steals the Jetpad. The Go Jetters give chase in the Grimbler, heading right into the eye of the storm.

24.title: The Valley of Balls, Kazakhstan
24.plot: Glitch is seeking the ideal ball to use to practice his bowling - something big and heavy. Can the Go Jetters take control of a rocky situation in the Valley of Balls?

25.title: Gliding, Argentina
25.plot: The Go Jet cadets are taking to the skies in Argentina. Meanwhile, Glitch gatecrashes their academy gliding test, causing calamity in the skies.

26.title: Nomads, Mongolia
26.plot: Glitch is out on a camping expedition in Mongolia. There's not much around except a group of Mongolian nomads. He visits their camp and inadvertently offends them, then his misfiring jetpack causes him to land on one of their precious horses, causing it to gallop away from the camp with Glitch on its back.

27.title: Go Jet Academy: Compass Navigators
27.plot: Kyan and Foz are working on their compass navigation skills and need to find the North Tower within a magnificent maze in order to pass their academy test.

28.title: Wolong Panda Reserve, China
28.plot: Lars and Foz are in the Wolong Nature Reserve in China, taking care of the 2,000 pandas that live in the wild there. Grim HQ has also landed in the Wolong reserve, having been through a monsoon. The rain has washed Grandmaster Glitch's ship sparkling clean.

29.title: Go Jet Academy: Map Readers
29.plot: At the Go Jet Academy, Ubercorn has found an old map that leads to the GO Dome of the Ancients.

30.title: The Boreal Forest, Canada
30.plot: Grandmaster Glitch's Grimbots really need some cuddles, so it's down to Glitch to find them a new teddy bear. Glitch knows that bears live in Ontario in Canada, so he heads there to try and find a nice cuddly bear.

31.title: Timgad Ruins, Algeria
31.plot: The Go Jetters travel to Algeria in north Africa to check out the ancient Timgad Ruins. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch's computer game controller has broken.

32.title: Everglades National Park, Florida
32.plot: The Go Jetters are visiting the Everglades National Park in Florida, USA. It's an area made up mainly of water with amazing wildlife living there. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is also at the Everglades enjoying a holiday with his Grimbots. He decides to stop and have a picnic by the water, which brings the alligators dangerously close to him and a boat full of tourists.

33.title: The Sphinx, Egypt
33.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is in need of a holiday, so he takes his Grimbots to Egypt for some rest and relaxation. Glitch is so relaxed that he falls asleep on his deckchair in the sand. The Grimbots want to play, so decide to bury him in the sand while he sleeps. Having so much fun burying Glitch, they decide to bury the Great Sphinx, one of the oldest statues in the world.

34.title: Go Jet Academy: Mudslide
34.plot: It's a very rainy day at the Go Jet Academy and the Go Jetters are in the training domes teaching the cadets some crucial Go Jetter skills.

35.title: The Great Pacific Garbage Patch
35.plot: A storm washes up lots of plastic litter onto the Go Jet Academy beach.

36.title: The Leshan Giant Buddha, China
36.plot: Inspired by the statue of the Giant Buddha of Leshan, Ubercorn teaches the Go Jetters all about mindfulness to help them to concentrate.

37.title: Kinderdijk, Netherlands
37.plot: It's a whirlwind of windmill excitement as the Go Jetters travel to Kinderdijk in the Netherlands to celebrate National Mill Day.

38.title: The Great Mosque of Djenne, Africa
38.plot: Grandmaster Glitch has been invited to Djenne in Mali, Africa, to visit the people and to see one of his favorite things at work - mud.

39.title: Wimbledon, England
39.plot: The Go Jetters are at Wimbledon, London, to watch the world's most famous tennis tournament. But just as they settle in to watch the doubles final, Grandmaster Glitch and his Grimbots gatecrash the court. Glitch is determined to win Wimbledon, but he is not adhering to any of the rules, and the umpire wants him to leave. But Glitch is staying put until he can play some tennis and win the tournament.

40.title: Cave of Crystals, Mexico
40.plot: While in Mexico, Glitch takes a short cut through the Cave of Crystals, a hidden space that contains some of the biggest crystals in the world. On his way through the cave the clumsy Grandmaster falls off one of the crystals and into a deep ravine.

41.title: Bishop Rock Lighthouse, Isles of Scilly
41.plot: It's a dark night and Glitch is flying his Grim HQ over the sea around the Isles of Scilly. He's in the middle of reading a bedtime story to his Grimbots when his lamp breaks. He needs a new light, and when he sees the Bishops Rock Lighthouse in the distance he demands that the Grimbots get him the bulb.

42.title: Go Jet Academy: Irrigation
42.plot: It's farming time at the Go Jet Academy and the Go Jetters are growing corn in a big field. Their crops need watering and so the team are putting up an irrigation system which will water all the crops in the field. Growing corn is a slow process, and Grandmaster Glitch doesn't want to wait for the crops to grow. He shoots them with his size ray to make them bigger.

43.title: Bird Migration, Spain and Africa
43.plot: The Go Jetters are on the Strait of Gibraltar in southern Spain, working with a team of conservationists to track and follow a group of baby storks on their journey from Spain to Africa. The storks are flying high above the sea towards Africa, but Grandmaster Glitch is also up in the air with his Grimbots working on their flying formation and nearly crashes into the migrating birds.

44.title: Whistler Mountain, Canada
44.plot: The Go Jetters are on Whistler Mountain in Canada, doing some skiing and checking out the amazing cable car. Kyan and Foz are about to have a go at the Go Jet Ski Challenge when Grandmaster Glitch comes along and wants to show them how it's done - but the sneaky Grandmaster cheats by using his jet pack to power him forward. The Grimbots try to help by messing with the controls of the cable car in the control room.

45.title: Solar E-Glitch
45.plot: At the Go Jet Academy, the Go Jetters are about to watch one of nature's most spectacular events - a solar eclipse. They watch in amazement through their pinhole projectors as the moon moves between the Earth and the sun and its shadow throws them into darkness. Grandmaster Glitch has made a giant solar panel shaped like a moustache to power his Grimbots.

46.title: Korowai Treehouses, Indonesia
46.plot: The Go Jetters have been invited by the Korowai tribe to visit their village in the rainforest of Papua in Indonesia. They are an ancient tribe who build their homes above the ground. Meanwhile, Grandmaster Glitch is also in the rainforest, trying to build the tallest treehouse in the world. When he sees that the Korowai's treehouse is even taller than his, he tries to get his even higher.

47.title: Go Jet Academy: Volcanic Island
47.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is drilling into the ground below the ocean near Academy Island, looking for bubbly mud that is heated up by an underground volcano. Back at the Academy, the Go Jetters have been monitoring the underground volcano and discover that it is showing more activity than usual. This is because Glitch has been drilling into it, and it could mean that the volcano is going to erupt.

48.title: Chocolate Hills, Philippines
48.plot: The Grimbots discover a place called the Chocolate Hills on Bohol Island in the Philippines and take him there. The Go Jetters are also heading to the Chocolate Hills, but when they get there they are shocked to discover that the hills are covered in real chocolate. Glitch has turned the Chocolate Hills into a chocolate theme park.

49.title: Go Jet Academy: Global Gameshow
49.plot: It's the Go Jetters as you've never seen them before as they take part in a disco-dazzling around the world gameshow. Foz and Xuli are on Team Go Jetter and Grandmaster Glitch and Kyan are on Team Glitch as they go head to head to see who will win. Ubercorn and Lars are the quizmasters asking the questions in this ultimate geographic quiz.

50.title: Horsetail Fall, California
50.plot: The Go Jetters have travelled to Horsetail Fall in the Yosemite National Park. It's a 300m-high waterfall made of melted snow. Once a year the setting sun lights up the water, making it glow like fire for just a few special minutes. This is called Firefall, and if there isn't enough water from the melting snow, Firefall doesn't happen. Unfortunately, Grandmaster Glitch has built a snow princess at the top of the fall and is using an ice machine to stop her melting.

51.title: Ilulissat, Greenland
51.plot: Grandmaster Glitch has taken his teddy, Cuddles, to Ilulissat in Greenland to show him the sights, but Cuddles falls out of Grim HQ and gets stuck in the snow. The Grimbots melt the ice around Cuddles, and Glitch then uses Grim HQ to pull up the massive chunk of ice and carry it into the air. The Go Jetters are also in Ilulissat trying to spot some whales. They learn that Ilulissat means iceberg and that an iceberg is a huge chunk of ice which forms on land and then breaks off into the sea.

52.title: Sami Reindeer Herding, Norway
52.plot: The Go Jetters are in snowy Norway to learn about the reindeer that are cared for by the local Sami people. In the spring the reindeer go on a very long journey called migration and as part of this journey they catch a ferry to take them to their warmer summer home. Grandmaster Glitch and the Grimbots are also in Norway, but their Grimbler scares the migrating reindeer and some of them run away from the herd. The Go Jetters need to keep them calm and get them back to the herd so they can finish their migration.

1.title: The Eiffel Tower, France
1.plot: Grandmaster Glitch steals the Eiffel tower to use as a TV aerial.

2.title: The Pyramids of Giza, Egypt
2.plot: Grandmaster Glitch steals the Great Pyramid of Giza to play his shape game.

3.title: Stonehenge, England
3.plot: Grandmaster Glitch decides to play giant dominoes with Stonehenge stones. Can the Go Jetters stop him?

4.title: The Sahara Desert, Africa
4.plot: When building a sandcastle around an oasis, Glitch threatens the safety of the touaregs and their camels.

5.title: Niagara Falls, Canada and USA
5.plot: Glitch blocks Niagara Falls to give Grim HQ a mud bath causing a hydroelectric power station to stop working.

6.title: Sydney Opera House, Australia
6.plot: Glitch steals the Sydney Opera House to compete in a yacht race.

7.title: The Statue of Liberty, USA
7.plot: Glitch decides to make the Statue of Liberty look like him, he also makes it fall right into the path of a passing ferry.

8.title: The Brandenburg Gate, Germany
8.plot: Glitch steals the Quadriga of the Brandenburg Gate to make himself a Carousel.

9.title: Lambert-Fisher Glacier, Antarctica
9.plot: Glitch threatens the Lambert Glacier while he is making an ice statue of himself.

10.title: Chichen Itza, Mexico
10.plot: Glitch's giant ball game threatens El Castillo, Chichen Itza.

11.title: The Great Wall of China
11.plot: Glitch and his Grimbots have a long race on the Great Wall of China.

12.title: The Leaning Tower of Pisa, Italy
12.plot: The Go Jetter race to fix the Leaning Tower of Pisa, but has it really been glitched?

13.title: Lake Titicaca, South America
13.plot: Grandmaster Glitch lands with a splash in Lake Titicaca.

14.title: The Colosseum, Italy
14.plot: Grandmaster Glitch goes to the Colloseum to race his grimbots. Can the Go Jetters stop him?

15.title: The Taj Mahal, India
15.plot: The grimbots and Glitch attach a bit of the Taj Mahal to Grim HQ.

16.title: Mount Etna, Italy
16.plot: Glitch makes popcorn in Mount Etna, but he blocks the volcano and endangers the farms on its slopes.

17.title: Table Mountain, South Africa
17.plot: Glitch wants to ski, so the Grimbots give Table Mountain a snowy peak, which threatens its rare plants.

18.title: The Northern Lights, Finland
18.plot: Ubercorn is excited to see the Northern Lights but Glitch's Grunge-Grimbler covers them with smoke.

19.title: The Amazon Rainforest, South America
19.plot: Glitch wants a picnic so he stops the rain in the Amazon rainforest, upsetting the local tree frogs.

20.title: The Dead Sea, Middle East
20.plot: The Go Jetters are relaxing by the Dead Sea when Grandmaster Glitch causes a catastrophe by dumping barrels of custard into the sea.

21.title: The Forbidden City, China
21.plot: Some runaway Chinese drums roll towards the Forbidden City, and it's up to the Go Jetters stop them.

22.title: The Wieliczka Salt Mine, Poland
22.plot: The Go Jetters have to save the famous Salt Statues from floods due to Glitch's digging when Glitch is trying to get salt for his chips.

23.title: Giant's Causeway, Northern Ireland
23.plot: A giant Grandmaster Glitch means big trouble for the Giant's Causeway, but can the Go Jetters help?

24.title: The Golden Gate Bridge, USA
24.plot: It is a very foggy day, and the Golden Gate Bridge foghorns are missing. Then they find out that Glitch has stolen them to use as horns for his Grimbler. Can the Go Jetters help?

25.title: Komodo National Park, Indonesia
25.plot: Glitch supersizes a fierce Komodo dragon, and the Go Jetters must find the sizeray to fix the glitch.

26.title: Big Ben, England
26.plot: Glitch removes Big Ben's bell on New Year's Eve.

27.title: The Strokkur Geyser, Iceland
27.plot: The geysers in Iceland are blocked. Glitch is to blame and it could cause an earthquake.

28.title: The Aqueduct of Segovia, Spain
28.plot: Glitch turns Segovia Aqueduct into a giant water slide and the Go Jetters must stop him from toppling it to the ground.

29.title: Rio de Janeiro, Brazil
29.plot: Glitch has stopped the samba at the Rio carnival. Will they stop him from ruining the carnival?

30.title: Mount Everest, Asia
30.plot: The Go Jetters are enjoying a calm day, apart from Kyan who wants to go on an adventure. He settles on climbing Mount Everest. Grandmaster Glitch is busy working on his mustache and crashes into Mount Everest. The Grimbots play in the snow and are joined by Glitch, who makes a giant snowball which starts rolling down the mountain with him on it. the Go Jetters stop the snowball from hitting some mountaineers by using GO Shield and GO Force. Glitch ends up in the snow but the Grimbots have escaped in GrimHQ and left him cold in the snow. The Go Jetters rescue him and ...

31.title: Loch Ness, Scotland
31.plot: A Grimbot is spying on the Go Jetters as they read stories about the Loch Ness monster. They all go to Loch Ness. The Go Jetters view a tranquil loch with a fisherman in a boat. All of a sudden the fisherman is dragged along by an unknown creature. He finally lets go of his rod and Xuli, using GO Dive, goes to investigate. She takes a photo and it is Grandmaster Glitch in the Grimbler. Glitch continues to dive towards the bottom hunting for Nessie but the Grimbler begins to break apart and it shoots back to the surface spilling oil. The Go Jetters use GO Grab and GO ...

32.title: The Grand Canyon, USA
32.plot: Kyan is wire-walking across the Grand Canyon as part of the GO Jetters training. Grandmaster Glitch fires his own wire across the canyon onto the the Grand Canyon Skywalk to try and beat Kyan. Grandmaster Glitch uses magnetic boots to walk across the wire. The Grimbots watch in admiration and play very loud music which causes the wires to vibrate leaving Kyan and Glitch hanging in danger, along with tourists on the Skywalk. Foz and Lars use GO Boots to support the Skywalk and to stop the loud music in the Grimbler. GO Fix is used by Lars to fix the Skywalk. Kyan then ...

33.title: Easter Island, Chile
33.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is on holiday on the Easter Island. He complains that there are too many tourists taking photos of the Moai statues and disturbing his rest. Glitch gets the Grimbots to build a new statue to distract the tourists but they are not impressed. The Grimbots have built a large pink poodle! Glitch breaks it and the broken pieces roll down a hill towards some tourists. The GO Jetters save them and also save the statues using GO Giant and GO Roll. One final piece of the poodle statue hits Glitch and knocks him off his chair.

34.title: The Parthenon, Greece
34.plot: Grandmaster Glitch is watching a James Bond film and he loves it. He thinks the only bad thing is that he was not in it. He starts making a film at the Parthenon. The film is based on Glitch beating the Go Jetters. The Grimbots are dressed up as the Go Jetters and Ubercorn and they have a cardboard Vroomster. Glitch wants to make it better and he tricks the Go Jetters by pretending the Grimbler is broken. The Go Jetters come to help and when they are distracted the Grimbots take the Vroomster. They then race around in it and keep knocking into the Parthenon. The Go ...

35.title: Saint Basil's Cathedral, Russia
35.plot: It is Grandmaster Glitch's birthday. The Grimbots make him a rubbish cake as he wanted one with green icing which looks a little like a castle. The Grimbots cover St Basil's Cathedral in green icing and Glitch loves it. Due to the cold weather the icing sets hard and traps some Cossack dancers inside. The Go Jetters come to help but the Grimbots trapped Lars and Foz in icing. Kyan distracts Glitch by joining some Cossack dancers to perform a birthday dance. Xuli uses GO Force set to heat to rescue Lars and Foz, who join her in melting the icing on the cathedral. It ...

36.title: Tarbela Dam, Pakistan
36.plot: When Grandmaster Glitch steals the G.O. Force, the forecast isn't good for the Tarbela Dam.

37.title: Mount Rushmore, USA
37.plot: The Grimbots add Glitch's face to one of the presidents on Mount Rushmore.

38.title: Caernarfon Castle, Wales
38.plot: In Wales, Glitch makes a lot of noise by using a shield as a musical instrument. How will the Go Jetters retrieve Xuli's treasured 'Academy Ace' flying trophy from Caernarfon Castle?

39.title: The Great Barrier Reef, Australia
39.plot: The team dives into action as Glitch's treasure hunt endangers the Great Barrier Reef.

40.title: Christmas Special: The North Pole, Arctic Ocean
40.plot: It's Christmas Eve and Santa's sleigh has vanished - can the Go Jetters save Christmas?

41.title: Hong Kong
41.plot: Glitch decides to create mini master toys. But they start to munch through everything in Hong Kong.

42.title: Waitomo Glowworm Caves, New Zealand
42.plot: It's Go Jetters glow when Glitch uses glow worms for his disco pizzazz in New Zealand.

43.title: Lake Retba, Senegal
43.plot: Glitch wants more strawberry milkshake so the grimbots suck up the pink water of Senegal's Milkshake Lake.

44.title: The Paddy Fields of China
44.plot: The Go Jetters swing into action when Glitch uses real landmarks for his crazy golf course.

45.title: Cappadocia, Turkey
45.plot: Glitch's game of hide-and-seek threatens to topple the fairy chimneys of Cappadocia in Turkey.

46.title: Maasai Mara National Park, Kenya
46.plot: The team roars into action as Glitch tries to take a selfie with a lion in the Maasai Mara.

47.title: The Gobi Desert, Mongolia
47.plot: Glitch and his grimbots are on the hunt for a super sized skeleton for their Museum of Grim and Gitch's giant drill causes a dino disaster for the team's fossil hunt in the Gobi Desert.

48.title: Bioluminescent Bay, Puerto Rico
48.plot: Glitch's bath time puts the creatures of Puerto Rico's Bioluminescent Bay in bubble-trouble.

49.title: The Blue Mountains, Jamaica
49.plot: Trouble brews in Jamaica when Glitch's campfire threatens a coffee plantation.

50.title: The Jigokudani Monkey Park, Japan
50.plot: The Go Jetters fly to the rescue in Japan, as Glitch is up to his usual monkey business.

51.title: The Nazca Lines, Peru
51.plot: The Go Jetters race to protect ancient artwork in Peru when Glitch sweeps the desert and erases the Nazca Lines.

imdb.title: Go Jetters
plot: Four explorers on a Global adventure. Xuli, Kyan, Lars, Foz. They are the _Go Jetters_ (qv)...!
synopsis: Go Jetters follows the adventures of four heroes, Xuli, Kyan, Lars and Foz, as they travel the world with their teacher, mentor and friend, Ubercorn.
